EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 032300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE WILL BE CENTRED TO THE W OF THE UK. OVER
SUNDAY NIGHT AND INTO MONDAY A CYCLONIC PATTERN WILL ESTABLISH ITSELF WITH
A SMALL-SCALE LOW LIKELY DEVELOPING IN THE N AND RUNNING SEWARD ACROSS THE
E OF THE UK EVENTUALLY BECMG 983 CENTRED TO THE W OF DENMARK BY MIDNIGHT
MONDAY INTO TUESDAY. AS THE LOW CONTINUES TO TRACK EWARD A N FLOW WILL BECOME
SET UP ACROSS THE UK. THROUGH TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY THERE IS UNCERTAINTY
IN THE PROGRESSION OF A TROUGH ACROSS SW UK EXTENDING FM A COMPLEX LOW-PRESSURE
SYSTEM IN THE ATLANTIC WHERE ONE OR MULTIPLE SMALL-SCALE LOWS MAY DEVELOP
AND SKIRT ACROSS THE S OF ENGLAND. ISOL GALES OR NEAR GALES MAY DEVELOP IN
THE SW APPROACHES AND CELTIC SEA AREAS AT TIMES ASSOCIATED WITH ANY CUT-OFF
LOWS THROUGH TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY OTHERWISE NO OTHER STRG WINDS FCST FOR
THIS PERIOD.
